From Jonathan G Harris Subject Re solvent for duct tape adhesive On benzene and Not only is benzene a carcinogen it is adsorbed through the skin and cause cumulative damage to the bone marrow which is essential to the production of your blood It is highly One exposure is unlikely to kill you but it will likely do hidden Benzene is one compound that chemists try like hell to avoid using Acetone is much less toxic but is highly flammable and It also dissolves lots of things so handle with great care Jonathan Harris Department of Chemical Engineering MIT Rm Ames Street Cambridge MA Fax